  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Doth our law judge any man,.... Or condemn any man; or can any man be lawfully condemned: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "before it hear him: what he has to say for himself; is this the usual process in our courts? or is this a legal one to condemn a man unheard? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and know what he doth? what his crimes are. This he said, having a secret respect for Christ, though he had not courage enough openly to appear for him. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and know what he doth? what his crimes are. This he said, having a secret respect for Christ, though he had not courage enough openly to appear for him. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "Doth our law judge any man, before it hear him, and know {n} what he doeth?",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Doth our law judge ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "i",
            "class": "",
            "text": "any",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " man, before it hear him, and know ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{n}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " what he doeth?",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(n) What the one who is accused has committed.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "51",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Doth our law",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ‘Law’ is emphatic. ‘You condemn the multitude for not knowing the law; but are we not forgetting the law in condemning a man unheard?’ These learned theologians and lawyers were forgetting such plain and simple texts as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 1:16-17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 17:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 19:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; involving the most elementary principles of justice.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "any man, before it hear him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Literally, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "the",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "man",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (prosecuted) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "except it first hear from himself",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
